Thus, the main goal of liberal feminism is the desire to gain equal rights in various spheres of life, to gain access to the state apparatus, the desire to make choices without obeying the will of a man. The course of liberal feminism can be divided into two waves. The first wave arose in the middle of the 19th century and lasted until the first third of the 20th century. The main requirement of the women's movement of this wave was the possibility of obtaining higher education. The labor issue was also the main important condition.